The paper deals with information inequalities and optimization problems, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of computer software to prove these inequalities suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The mention of capacity regions and rate-distortion functions suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the application of the technique to cases where the inequality holds due to statistical models suggests a connection to statistics (cs.SI).
